title: File:25-4 Papua New Guinea Repatriation Ceremony (9337945).jpg
author: U.S. Marine Corps photo by Cpl. Stephen Holland
description: Marines with the U.S. Embassy Port Moresby participate in a repatriation ceremony Sept. 24, 2025, in Port Moresby, Papua New Guinea. The ceremony marked the official transfer of possible remains discovered during the most recent recovery mission in the country. The remains were sent to the Defense POW/MIA Accounting Agency laboratory on Joint Base Pearl Harbor-Hickam in Hawaii for scientific analysis and possible identification. (U.S. Marine Corps photo by Cpl. Stephen Holland)
